snippet: Penn State opened preseason practice, and Coach Bill O’Brien said he was “very confident” the players who showed up were committed for the season.
abstract: Penn State football team holds its first official workout since sanctions were leveled against it by the NCAA and nine players transferred to play elsewhere; other Penn State items noted.
lead_paragraph: Penn State opened preseason practice, and Coach Bill O’Brien said he was “very confident” the players who showed up were committed for the season.

headline.main: Penn State Holds First Workout After Sanctions
headline.print_headline: Penn State Holds Workout, Its First One After Sanctions
